<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARMS SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The ironies of the "news" paper. On the one hand, we read about talks for 
treaties of peace between Arabs and Jews, and talks for treaties having to do 
with nuclear disarmament.Then we read that "the industrial powers flock to this 
small but wealthy nation in the post-Cold War push to sell weapons" ("Targeting 
Taiwan for Arms Deals," March 14). 
</P>
<P>
 We arm small nations to the teeth and then expect peace. If it were impossible 
for nations to acquire arms, then they could only attack each other with rocks 
and sticks. Why is it legal for any nation to produce and sell arms? They (the 
buyers) should be spending that money on building or rebuilding their 
infrastructures, their industrial bases, and above all else, their educational 
systems, not wasting it on weapons. 
</P>
<P>
 Why are we not in the midst of treaty talks that ban the production of all 
weapons, and the trade between nations of same? 
</P>
<P>
 PRESTON COSGROVE 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
