<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAKE RECOVERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * "Quake Seen Speeding Recovery of Economy" (March 7) adds an entirely new 
dimension to the term oxymoron .The "facts" and opinions set forth therein 
would lead one logically to conclude that to facilitate a rapid and complete 
recovery, what this economy really needs is for the "Big One" to materialize 
and totally devastate the entire Southern California area. One salivates in 
contemplation of the massive assistance for which the survivors might be 
eligible in the aftermath of that catastrophe. 
</P>
<P>
 This kind of reasoning is about on a par with that of the military genius who 
concluded during the Vietnam fiasco that the only way to save a village was to 
destroy it. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT S. COUGHLIN 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
</TEXT>
