 The Fresno County grand jury charged that nine Fresno State football players 
applied for food stamps, claiming they were homeless. The grand jury also 
charged that someone in the university's athletic department knew in December 
of 1992 about the applications, but failed to make the players pay back any 
benefits they had received. College Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Kidd, California's All-American point guard, has called a news 
