<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO TEARS FOR LANDLORD COUPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Subject: the March 8 article by H.G. Reza, "Some Apartment Owners on Shaky 
Financial Ground." 
</P>
<P>
 Really, my heart bleeds for Sally and Jack Nissenbaum for their apartment 
problems.Reza should have done his homework. I would like to be in the same 
place as these "unfortunate" landlords. 
</P>
<P>
 With 50 units at approximately $600 per unit, their return is $30,000 per 
month. With a mortgage of $12,000 per month, not a bad return. 
</P>
<P>
 They bought the place in 1979. So tell me, with all the profit they have made 
since 1979, why should I bleed? 
</P>
<P>
 Don't get me wrong, I do not like to see anyone suffer. However, there are 
individuals that have never had that kind of an income, or will ever have it. A 
payday-to-payday existence for most. 
</P>
<P>
 For 15 years the Nissenbaums have had a very nice, secure return on their 
units. Nothing is forever. 
</P>
<P>
 FRED L. WOLF 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 
</P>
</TEXT>
