<HEADLINE>
<P>
WITH OR WITHOUT PARENTS: MADELINE RIDES TO THE RESCUE IN NEW GOLDEN BOOK VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNNE HEFFLEY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Madeline, Ludwig, Bemelmans' endearing children's book heroine, has been 
around for almost half a century, but her ageless charm is evident in an 
effervescent new holiday Golden Book Video. 
</P>
<P>
 In "Madeline and the Easter Bonnet," the little French girl designs an Easter 
hat for Bon-Bon the milk-wagon horse, who's had the blues over her old tattered 
chapeau.The unusual hat, complete with miniature Eiffel Tower, causes a stir 
when it is whisked into a fashionable shop by an errant breeze, but Bon-Bon is 
so desolate over its loss that she refuses to make her Paris deliveries. 
Madeline and friends save the day, of course, and are the sensation of an 
Easter fashion show, too. Golden Book Video. $12.95. 
</P>
<P>
 Parent Alert: Homework blues, TV overload, bad dream monsters: If these and 
other common parental concerns about your preschool and school-age children are 
giving you high anxiety, check out a new line of truly helpful self-help 
parenting audiotapes from Achievement Inc., a subsidiary of educational 
publisher Focus Media Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Easy to understand, supportive narrative and vignettes impart a wealth of 
workable tips and advice from nationally recognized educators, psychologists 
and child care experts.  
</P>
<P>
 Prices: $7.95 to $14.95. Information: (800) 645-8989. 
</P>
<P>
 Morphin Madness: OK, OK, we hate to encourage this, but for the legion of 
hard-core fans of Fox Television's "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers" out there who 
can't get enough of their karate-chopping superheroes and Rita Repulsa, the 
laughable lip-syncing villainess, look for the five-part "Green Ranger" series 
on home video, starting Wednesday. The tapes, released by Saban Entertainment 
through PolyGram Video, will be available in retail outlets for $12.95 each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
