<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; STATE NAMES DRAMA TEACHER TO ARTS PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A drama teacher who has taught at Tustin High School for more than 20 years 
has been appointed to a state panel that reviews and offers changes to the high 
school visual and performing arts curriculum. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Roseman was named to the Visual and Performing Arts Curriculum Framework 
Criteria Committee recently by the California State Board of Education. She and 
other panel members will meet throughout the year to work on developing the 
state curriculum. 
</P>
<P>
 Roseman was the Tustin Unified School District's Teacher of the Year in 1989. 
She was one of four Orange County teachers who competed in the California 
Teacher of the Year competition that year.BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
