<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAKE FOREST; COUNCIL TO DISCUSS DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The hail of bullets didn't hit anyone, but a botched drive-by shooting last 
week has prompted a special City Council meeting at 5 p.m. today to deal with 
gang problems. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will hear about the community's concerns and discuss what City 
Hall can do to help Orange County sheriff's investigators find whomever fired a 
gun from a passing car on Tama Lane last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Ann Van Haun said investigators suspect there were gang ties in 
the drive-by incident and that local students may be involved. 
</P>
<P>
 "We called the meeting to talk about what we can do to help," she said. "We're 
not going to stand by and not do anything." 
</P>
<P>
 Van Haun said that options before the council range from offering a reward for 
information leading to the gunman's arrest to discussing with school 
administrators ways the city might ease gang-related problems. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to take a stand right here," said Van Haun. "We don't want to 
wait for things to get worse." FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
