<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; BANDS NOT PERMITTED TO PRACTICE AT PUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The owner of O'Leary's Pub said those bands playing at his bar were only 
practicing. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said rehearsals or no, the bands were providing live 
entertainment -- and O'Leary's doesn't have a permit for that. 
</P>
<P>
 Ever since the council revoked a permit for live entertainment from O'Leary's 
Pub six months ago, officials said, owner Ronald Slutsky has continued to 
provide such entertainment on weekends. 
</P>
<P>
 His permit allows Slutsky to provide entertainment in the form of a jukebox, a 
pool table and a dart game only. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have not violated the permit," Slutsky said recently. "The bands practice. 
I don't pay them." 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Steven C. Anderson responded: "Mr. Slutsky's playing word games 
with us." 
</P>
<P>
 Council members have decided to allow Slutsky to continue operating his bar 
with "absolutely no live entertainment, practicing, rehearsing or playing." 
</P>
<P>
 The council also required that Slutsky's permit be reviewed in 90 days. MIMI 
KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
