<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAROLED KILLER CHARGED WITH MOLESTING 4-YEAR-OLD GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A convicted killer and sex offender who was released from prison over the 
objections of his victims' relatives was arraigned Monday on charges of 
molesting a 4-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
 Russell Obremski did not enter a plea during his brief court appearance.He was 
ordered held without bail on charges of sex abuse and sodomy. 
</P>
<P>
 Obremski spent 24 years in prison for the 1969 killings of two women in 
southern Oregon before being paroled 4 1/2 months ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Obremski, 49, was on parole from a 20-year sentence for the statutory rape of 
a 14-year-old girl in Washington state when he murdered Laverna May Lowe and 
Betty Ann Ritchie. 
</P>
<P>
 He was sentenced to two life prison terms. His parole was delayed five times 
as relatives of his victims campaigned to keep him in prison. He was released 
Nov. 8. 
</P>
