<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James M. Gomez, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interpore Device OKd: Interpore International has received some long-awaited 
news from the federal government. 
</P>
<P>
 After waiting for almost two years, Interpore, a maker of artificial bone and 
dental materials, received word from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration on 
Monday that it can sell an implantable device to dentists. 
</P>
<P>
 The device is a three-millimeter-wide pole that is embedded in a patient's 
jawbone and used to anchor artificial teeth to the gum line, making dentures 
obsolete. 
</P>
