<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: HOME SALES RISE FOR 7TH MONTH AS PRICES STABILIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home sales in Ventura County rose in February for the seventh month in a row, 
and the falling prices of recent years may finally be leveling off. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 550 new and resold homes closed escrow last month -- 23% more than 
in February, 1993, according to Dataquick Information Systems.The median 
selling price in February was $193,000, 3% above the year-earlier figure. 
</P>
<P>
 "People seem to feel that both prices and interest rates have bottomed out," 
says John Karevoll, a financial analyst with La Jolla-based Dataquick. "That 
perception, along with an improving economy, are bringing buyers into the 
market." 
</P>
<P>
 Seventy-two new homes were sold in the county last month, twice as many as a 
year earlier and 16% more than in January, 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 Among resales, escrow closed on 390 single-family houses last month, up 19% 
from February, 1993, and 16% more than in January of this year. Condominium 
resales last month totaled 88, 6% more than a year earlier and 16% above 
January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
