<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: BIOPOOL INTERNATIONAL'S PROFITS TUMBLE IN '93 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biopool International Inc., a Ventura maker of test kits for diagnosing blood 
disorders, said its profit increased 6% in the fourth quarter but its profits 
suffered a significant decline for 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the quarter ended Dec. 31, Biopool reported a profit of $198,993, compared 
with earnings of $188,292 for the same period a year earlier.Revenue in the 
latest quarter rose 16% to $1.11 million, from $956,898. 
</P>
<P>
 But for all of 1993, Biopool's profit fell 42% to $360,729, from $626,670 for 
the previous year. Revenue for 1993 totaled $4.31 million, down 11% from $4.87 
million. Biopool said its performance in 1993 was hurt by the unfavorable 
exchange rate of the Swedish krona, which resulted in reduced revenue at the 
company's Swedish subsidiary, Biopool AB. 
