FUND SET UP FOR ATHLETE INJURED BY GOLF BALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fund to help pay medical expenses has been established for Ashley Bethel, 
the 14-year-old Lake Forest track and field standout who lost her right eye 
when she was struck by a golf ball Feb. 23 at Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bethel family has paid about $13,000 for Ashley's initial treatment and 
surgery to remove the eye and expects to incur another $5,000 in medical 
expenses to have a glass prosthesis implanted next month. 
</P>
<P>
 Bethel, a two-time national youth pentathlon champion, expects to return to 
Los Alisos School today. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations can be sent to the Ashley Bethel Fund, c/o Wells Fargo Bank; 24251 
Rockfield Blvd.; Lake Forest, 92630. 
