<HEADLINE>
<P>
E.T. PHONE HOME -- IF YOU NEED A NEW SCRIPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Before the ceremonies began Monday night, hundreds of fans were gathered in 
front of the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion. There was the usual smattering of 
protesters representing religious and anti-abortion positions, but none of the 
chanting that accompanied protests in previous years. 
</P>
<P>
 The biggest attention-getter was a plane that flew above the Music Center 
trailing a banner that advertised "the world's funniest script" and, of course, 
a phone number. 
</P>
