<HEADLINE>
<P>
KOCE DRIVE DRAWS RECORD REVENUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County public television station KOCE-TV Channel 50 completed its most 
successful membership drive ever on Sunday, raising $295,431 according to a 
preliminary estimate, station spokeswoman Judith Schaefer said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The response to the 18-day campaign was attributed to special programming that 
included a taped concert by New-Age singer Yanni, as well as to a one-day 
extension of the spring drive, Schaefer said. 
</P>
<P>
 The drive brought in almost 27% more than last spring's record-setting 
$232,803 during a 17-day campaign. ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
