<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN JAILED AFTER RAFT IS SHOT ON LAKE; CRIME: SUNBATHER IS UNHURT AS INFLATABLE 
DEVICE IS SUNK. TRANSIENT IS ARRESTED AFTER EIGHT-MILE FREEWAY CHASE. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An inflatable raft was shot out from under a bather on Lake Elizabeth Monday 
and a 43-year-old transient was arrested a short time later, after leading 
police on an eight-mile freeway chase. 
</P>
<P>
 Enzo Orello was taken into custody by the California Highway Patrol after he 
was spotted traveling northbound on the Golden State Freeway in a van matching 
the description of the vehicle used by a gunman who sank the raft with several 
shots at about 8:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified man in the raft was not injured in the attack and was able to 
swim to shore, authorities said.He gave authorities a description of both the 
armed suspect he saw standing on the bank and of the van the suspect drove off 
in, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP Officer Brian Lottermoser said he saw Orello make an illegal lane change 
on the freeway and believed the van matched the description of the vehicle that 
had been identified as the suspect's. 
</P>
<P>
 Lottermoser said he chased Orello eight miles north on the Golden State 
Freeway before Orello pulled over and was arrested without incident. The CHP 
knew of no motive for the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Orello was booked on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon at the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff Department's Santa Clarita station. His bail was set at 
$55,000, authorities said. 
</P>
