<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: LONDON; A JEWEL IN THE TOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Queen Elizabeth II will open the new Jewel House at the Tower of London on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Fiber-optic lighting and Italian-made glass showcases will let visitors have a 
closer look at the Crown Jewels, a major tourist draw, than before. 
</P>
<P>
 In the new showcases, some of the jewels will be within 18 inches of the 
viewing window. Previously, four feet was the closest distance. 
</P>
<P>
 The larger, heavier security Jewel House cost about $1.5 million to build and 
will accommodate up to 20,000 visitors a day. Admission is $11. 
</P>
